Ten years ago, I started as a simple seller on Amazon. 

Don’t get me wrong - I still sell on Amazon, but now, life has taken a surprising turn. 

I’m sitting as a judge on Amazon’s ‘Mission Start ab’. It feels like a dream. My own journey, from starting Wow to this moment, shows that hard work pays off.

‘Mission Start Ab’ is a chance for me to help others grow their dreams. I’ve been there, struggling and learning. Now, I want to give back, help new entrepreneurs. This show is not just about business. It’s about big dreams and making them real.

To everyone out there working hard: your efforts will take you places. Your story is still being written. If I could make it, so can you. Keep going.

Degrees alone are no longer enough—skills are what truly set you apart. In today’s world, opportunities come to those who can prove their expertise, not just their qualifications.

As startups continue to rise across the nation, the demand for skilled individuals will only grow. 

The future belongs to those who learn, adapt, and build real value. It’s time to focus on what you can do, not just what’s on paper.

Founders don’t just hire for skills; they look for mindset and attitude. 

Being adaptable shows that you can handle change and thrive in any situation. Accountability means taking ownership of your work. A high emotional intelligence helps you navigate relationships, handle feedback, and work effectively in a team.

Master these qualities, and you won’t just fit in—you’ll stand out.

Taking a leave is normal, but lying about it can harm your credibility in the long run. 

Trust is a two-way street—employees should be honest about their needs, and employers should be understanding enough to grant leaves when genuinely required.

In my opinion, a workplace thrives when there is mutual respect and transparency.

Having a great product isn’t enough!  Many businesses fail despite offering something amazing. Why? Poor marketing, bad timing, weak execution, or lack of customer demand. 

Success isn’t just about what you sell. Focus on market research, branding, and building the right strategy. Adapt, learn, and grow!

Beast gaming is a whole new level of vast and unpredictable. One person handling it all? Almost impossible.

Content creation is no longer a side hustle; it’s the next big industry. The ones who innovate, adapt, and stay ahead will define entertainment in ways we’ve never seen before.

Not every podcast is worth your time. Jumping on every mic won’t grow your business—sales will.

 A few reputed platforms can boost your image, but the rest are just noise. Prioritize building your brand and delivering results over endless PR. 

Focus on creating impact, not just conversation.

Sometimes, the best marketing requires no effort at all! When NASA’s Mars mission captured global attention, sales of Mars chocolate bars saw a surprising surge. 

This phenomenon, shows how a brand can benefit simply from relevance and association.

For businesses, the key takeaway is clear—timing and positioning matter. Aligning your brand with trending events, even indirectly, can create organic demand. 

Stay aware of cultural moments, and you might just find your own unexpected marketing boost.

Cutting your circle isn’t about negativity; it’s about making space for those who truly add value to your life.

The people who celebrate your growth, stand by you in difficult times, and push you to be better are the ones who matter. A small circle of genuine friends will always be more meaningful than a large group that doesn’t have your best interests at heart.

Letting go isn’t easy, but it’s necessary for personal growth and peace. Choose quality over quantity.
